==Japanese==

===Etymology 1===
Originally a compound of {{etyl|ojp|ja}} elements {{compound|lang=ja|こ|tr1=ko|t1=(''pronoun'') this|の|tr2=no|t2=possessive, modifies following noun}}.  {{l|ja|こ}} as a pronoun is no longer used individually in modern Japanese.

====Pronunciation====
* {{l|ja|sc=Latn|訓読み|Kun'yomi}}
* {{IPA|lang=ja|[ko̞no̞]}}

====Alternative forms====
* {{l|ja|此の}}, {{l|ja|斯の}}

====Adnominal====
{{ja-pos|h|adnominal|rom=kono}}

# ''([[deictically]])'' [[this]] ... (near the speaker)
#: {{usex|lang=ja|'''この'''車は緑です。|tr='''この'''くるまはみどりです。<br/>'''''Kono''' kuruma wa midori desu.''|t='''This''' car is green.}}
# ''([[anaphorically]])'' [[this]] ... I am talking about (only the speaker knows)

=====Usage notes=====
This term can only be used when followed by a noun or noun phrase.  It cannot be used as a standalone pronoun.  Examples:
* *'''この'''がすきです。 — *'''''Kono''' ga suki desu.'' — I like this ... — '''incorrect''': there must be a noun in place of the ...
:: Using ''kono'' as above is a bit like using English {{term|lang=en|the}} without a noun after it.
* '''この'''いろがすきです。 — '''''Kono''' iro ga suki desu.'' — I like this color. — '''correct''': a noun follows ''kono''.

Almost always spelled in hiragana as {{Jpan|この}}.

