===Etymology 2===
{{IPAchar|/kokonotsu/}} > {{IPAchar|/kono/}}

Abbreviation of ''[[kokonotsu]]'' (“nine”).

====Pronunciation====
* {{l|ja|sc=Latn|訓読み|Kun'yomi}}
* {{IPA|lang=ja|[ko̞no̞]}}

====Alternative forms====
* {{l|ja|九}}

====Number====
{{ja-pos|h|number|rom=kono}}

# {{dated|lang=ja}} [[nine]]
#: {{usex|lang=ja|ひい、ふう、みい、よう、いつ、むう、なな、やあ、'''この'''、とお。|tr=''hī, fū, mī, yō, itsu, mū, nana, yā, '''kono''', tō.''|t=One, two, three, four, five, six, seven, eight, '''nine''', ten.}}

=====Usage notes=====
Generally only used when counting out loud, as in the example above.  In writing, usually found spelled out in hiragana as {{Jpan|この}} to make the reading unambiguous.

